Commentary.Commentary: We are back for Australia's inning.  David Warner and Marcus Harris are the openers. James Anderson to start with the new ball. Here we go ...

Apart from Root, no one showed any composure. Although the skipper, fell after making his fifty, the other batsmen got a start but fail to stay in the middle and convert it into a big store. Ollie Robinson and Jack Leach hit some crucial runs and now it is up to the bowlers of England to set the tone for their team. Around 20 overs are still left in today's play and England have to scalp wickets and end the day on a positive note. Stay tuned as we will be back with Australia's inning.

Another successful bowling display from Australia. All of them have a wicket to their name and they have bundled out England for just 185 runs. After winning the toss and electing to bowl first, the bowlers stepped up to the occasion and it was Pat Cummins who set the tone. Then Mitchell Starc took the dangerous wicket of Root and Bairstow. Scott Boland got his maiden Test wicket and as the tail started to wag a bit more. Nathan Lyon came back and swept them away.

OUT! Nathan Lyon sends Ollie Robinson back to the hut. He grabs the final wicket and England are all out. Nathan Lyon serves a fuller-length delivery, on middle. Ollie Robinson advances down the pitch and heaves it towards deep mid-wicket. Scott Boland takes a sharp catch there. England are all out for 185.
Commentary.Howout: c Scott Boland b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Fullish delivery, outside off. James Anderson looks to drive but gets beaten.
A low full toss ball, on the pads. Ollie Robinson works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a length, down leg. Ollie Robinson bends and lets the ball go through.
Back of a length again, around leg. Ollie Robinson moves on the leg side and hits it uppishly towards mid on. No run there.

FOUR! Another boundary! An unusual shot by Ollie Robinson. Mitchell Starc goes short this time, around middle. Ollie Robinson makes room and slashes it through the outer half of his bat. The ball flies past gully for a cheeky boundary.
FOUR! Ollie Robinson trying to some quick runs. Mitchell Starc serves an overpitched delivery, around middle. Ollie Robinson makes room and whips it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller now, on middle. James Anderson tucks it off the inner half to square leg. James Anderson survives this over.
Short and angling on middle. James Anderson punches off the back foot to point.
Flatter and outside off. James Anderson prods and punches it on the off side.
James Anderson is the last man to come out in the middle.

OUT! TAKEN! Nathan Lyon gets his second wicket! Lyon gives nice flight to this and angles it on middle. Jack Leach lunges to defend but gets a thick outside edge to the first slip fielder where Steven Smith takes it.
Commentary.Howout: c Steven Smith b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up, full and on middle. Jack Leach pushes it to silly point who gets hit on the body but was on a bounce.
A loopy ball, on middle. Ollie Robinson eases it down to long on for one run.
A length ball, outside off. Leach looks to drive but misses it.
Serves a short ball, on middle. Leach shuffles across and sits under it.
Touch fuller, on off, pushed to covers.
On a length, outside off. Leach shoulders arms to it.
On a length, on off. Leach pushes it back to Starc who gets low to grab it.
Length ball, on the pads, this is flicked to deep square leg for a brace.
Slower, short and on off. Ollie Robinson defends it off the back foot. 11 runs coming off the over.
Jack Leach is targeting Lyon here! A full ball, outside off. Leach drives it hard through covers and take three runs.
Around off, pushed to covers.
SIX! This time he middles it. A full ball, on middle. Leach thumps it straight down the ground for a biggie.
Full and on middle. Jack Leach smashes it high in the air and towards long on, does not middle it and Cameron Green cuts it off. Two.
A flighted ball, outside off. Leach gets on the front foot as he looks to push and does it just wide of silly point.
On a length, on middle. Ollie Robinson defends it back to the bowler.
Starc serves yet another short ball, on middle. Ollie Robinson is not interested to play and sits under it.
Short in length, outside off. Ollie Robinson sways away from the line of the ball.
On a length, on off. Ollie Robinson again tries to work it on the leg side but manages to get an inside edge onto the pads.
Two Leg Byes!  Length and on the pads. Ollie Robinson tickles it fine to the fine leg region for a brace. It went off the pads.
In the air and it falls safely! A length ball, on middle. Ollie Robinson looks to flick but closes his bat face too early. It takes the leading edge and drops safe near short cover.
Tossed up, on off. Leach prods and defends it on the off side.
A full ball, on middle. Leach skips down and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, outside off. Jack Leach blocks it towards point.
Loopy delivery, outside off. Ollie Robinson drives it uppishly towards mid-on. A single taken.
A replica of the previous one. Nathan Lyon tosses it up, on off. Ollie Robinson defends it out.
Loopy delivery, outside off. Ollie Robinson lunges and blocks it out.
A length ball, outside off. Leach rocks back and leaves it alone. He survives this delivery.

Oh, dear! Mitchell Starc almost had Jack Leach. A full delivery, angling on the off stump. Jack Leach under-edges this one on to the crease, the ball bounces over the stumps. Jack Leach gets lucky here.
Jack Leach walks out to the middle.

OUT! Mitchell Starc has his man! England's final hope departs! Mitchell Starc serves a short ball this time, it does not bounce as much as Bairstow expected, over middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow leans back and tries to back away but the ball deflects off his glove and flies to the man at gully. Cameron Green dives forward and takes a sharp catch to dismiss Jonny Bairstow who was just about to get going.
Commentary.Howout: c Cameron Green b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Oh, shot! Jonny Bairstow you beauty! That is one of the best shots we have seen today. Mitchell Starc overcooks this delivery, outside off. Jonny Bairstow drives it beautifully past mid off for a boundary. Perfect timing on that.
On a length, down the leg. Jonny Bairstow misses his flick and it goes through to the keeper.

Mitchell Starc overpitches this one, on off. Ollie Robinson punches it down the ground again. This time he drives it past mid on. The ball won't race away towards the boundary ropes, but the batters pick up three runs.
Mitchell Starc (11-2-36-1) is back on.
Length delivery again, darting it on the pads. Ollie Robinson pushes it towards fine leg for a run.
Tad fuller again, on the pads this time. Jonny Bairstow tucks it square on the leg side. A single taken.
Change of length this time, short, on the body. Ollie Robinson, on back foot, pulls it gently towards deep mid-wicket for three runs.
FOUR! Beautifully driven! Scott Boland serves a fuller-length delivery, outside off. Ollie Robinson punches it down the ground past the mid off fielder for a boundary. England much more of that.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Ollie Robinson blocks it towards short leg.
Length delivery, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it to covers and scampers through to the other end.
Short delivery, on the body. Ollie Robinson defends it out solidly off the back foot.
Short in length again, down leg. Ollie Robinson ducks under it and lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. Ollie Robinson guides it to gully. No run there.
Tad shorter this time, on the body. Jonny Bairstow pulls it towards deep mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Length again, on middle. Jonny Bairstow blocks it watchfully.
On a length, nipping back in onto the pads. Jonny Bairstow looks to play this but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Good-length, outside off. Ollie Robinson leans forward and blocks it to gully.
Ollie Robinson is the new man in.

Review time! Scott Boland has to wait a little bit more to celebrate his first wicket in Test. Wood takes the review after given LBW out. HotSpot shows pad first and the third umpire says it is clearly pad first. Three reds and now Scott Boland and the MCG celebrates his first wicket. What a moment for Boland!

OUT! LBW! Scott Boland gets his maiden Test wicket! Mark Wood departs early in the innings. Scott Boland serves a length ball, angling it into the pads. Mark Wood looks to flick,with bat and pad together but mistimes his flick and gets rapped on the pads. A huge appeal by England and the umpire raises his finger. Mark Wood thinks otherwise and goes for the review. Snicko shows that the ball hit the pad first and Ball Tracker shows three reds. The decision stands and England lose a review and a wicket. Scott Boland gets all the applause from the MCG and his teammates as well. A moment to remember for him.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Scott Boland

Commentary.Commentary: Length delivery, outside off. Mark Wood guides towards gully. No run there.

Length ball, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow tucks it towards fine leg and scampers through to the other end. Bairstow was looking for the second run, but loses his balance on his way and the batters will settle for a single.
Short of a length this time, down leg. Jonny Bairstow looks to pull but fails to get any bat on it.
A length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow shuffles across and lets it through.
Short in length, on middle. Wood pulls it with soft hands, wide of deep square leg for a brace.
The pace is getting bigger on Wood but he is surviving well. On a length, on middle. Wood blocks it on the leg side.
On a length, on middle. Wood solidly blocks it.
Short ball, on middle. Wood tries to ride it as he looks to pull but misses it completely.
Extra bounce yet again. Wood defends it to point.
A full ball, slanting on off. Wood pushes it nicely on the off side.
Length and on off, pushed to mid off.
On a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow keeps it out.
FOUR! Edgy runs! A length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to push but gets an inside edge and the ball races away to the fine leg fence.
On a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow opens the face of the bat and guides it to the gully region, all along the ground.
This was on a length and way outside off. Jonny Bairstow leaves it with ease.
A length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow hangs back and punches it to covers.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.

A huge appeal for LBW but not given. Pat Cummins chats with Nathan Lyon who is standing across and opts not to take the review. A length ball, angling on middle. Mark Wood looks to defend under his eyes but misses and gets hit on the pads. Height might have saved him.
On a length, on off. Mark Wood defends it towards cover.
A pacy short ball, on middle. Mark Wood gets the taste of his own medicine but leaves it alone in the end.
A length ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Pat Cummins is back into the attack.
Good-length delivery, outside off, at 136.4 clicks. Jonny Bairstow offers no shot on that.
A short ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow solidly defends it.
Nicely driven and now Wood is off the mark. A full ball way outside off. Wood drives it through covers for three runs. The fielder chases it back and keeps it down to three.
A flighted ball, on middle. Wood stays back and defends it to short leg.
A tossed up ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow drills it down to long on for a single.
We are back for the last session of the day. Mark Wood joins Jonny Bairstow in the middle. Nathan Lyon will continue with the ball. Here we go..
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

Pat Cummins and his men continue to demolish England's batting order. Mitchell Starc got the prized scalp of Joe Root and sent him back to the hut after he scored his fifty. Stokes and Bairstow tried to steady the ship there in the middle but could not hold on too long as Stokes was dismissed by Cameron Green. Bairstow looks good there in the middle and he would be the last hope for England. Just like the previous session, England lost a wicket at the end of this session as well. As Jos Buttler threw his wicket away to put England in deeper troubles. Australia will be looking to bundle out England as early as possible. While England will be hoping for Jonny Bairstow to guide England to a decent first innings total.
Australia stay on top after yet another session. They picked up three big wickets and continued their dominance. England continue to sink further and are ending this session with 6 wickets down.

OUT! TAKEN! England are 6 down now and the umpire calls the end to this session as well. A loopy ball, on off. Jos Buttler comes down the track, does not reach to the pitch of the ball but still swings across the line. He drags it and hits it high towards deep square leg where Scott Boland settles under it and takes a good catch. That will also be Tea on Day 1.
Commentary.Howout: c Scott Boland b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Short, straight and outside off. Jos Buttler watches it all the way to the keeper.
This one stays a bit low, full and outside off. Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone.
A short pacy ball, on middle, the ball swivels in the air through to the keeper. Jonny Bairstow sits under it.
A length ball, angling outside off. Jonny Bairstow shoulders arms to it.
Halt in play. Looks like we have a pitch invader. The MCG is loving it as they cheer for him but the umpires do not. The security is dealing with it and we have a little break here.
On middle, on a length. Defended out.
Slight hesitation but no harm done. Around off. Jonny Bairstow taps it to backward point. He first calls for a quick single but in the end, denies it.
A length ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Full-length, outside off. Jos Buttler drives it to mid off.
Back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Jonny Bairstow leans back and plays an upper-cut over backward point. Three runs taken.
Good-length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow hangs back and defends it out.
Short of a length, just outside the off pole. Jonny Bairstow looks to cut that but gets an under-edge towards slips.
Goes full again this time on the pads. Jonny Bairstow dabs it to mid-wicket.
Fuller in length, darting it on the off stump. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to mid off.
Full-length, around the fourth pole. Jos Buttler leaves that alone.
On a length, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow flicks it to mid-wicket. A single taken.
Drops it short, around leg. Jonny Bairstow ducks under it.
Overpitches it, on the pads. Jos Buttler clips it past mid-wicket for three runs. Jos Buttler gets off the mark with that triple!
Full-length again, on middle. Jos Buttler blocks it out.
Tad fuller, outside off. Jos Buttler lets that through to the keeper.
Changes from both the ends now as Pat Cummins comes back into the attack.
A length ball, outside off, at 139.2 clicks. Jonny Bairstow shoulders arms.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to point. No run there.
FOUR! Mitchell Starc drops this short, down the leg. Jonny Bairstow goes for the big hook, but get a glove past the keeper all the way towards fine leg fence for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow stands tall and blocks it on the off side.
Full in length, outside the off pole. Jonny Bairstow offers no shot.
Tad fuller, darting it on the pads. Jonny Bairstow clips it to square leg for a brace.
Mitchell Starc is back into the attack.
Pitching it up, outside off. Jos Buttler lets that go. A wicket maiden by Cameron Green.
Fuller in length, drifting down the leg. Jos Buttler misses his flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.

Oh, dear! A Jaffa by Cameron Green. That misses everything. A length ball, angling it into Buttler. Jos Buttler looks to drive this but gets beaten and the ball nips back in sharply. It goes through the gap between bat and pad and over the stumps. Close call there.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Jos Buttler leaves that alone.
Jos Buttler is the new man in.

OUT! Cameron Green strikes and he has got a huge wicket here. Ben Stokes has to go back to the hut. Cameron Green serves a back-of-a-length delivery, around off. Ben Stokes leans back and goes for the upper-cut, but only manages to get an edge to Nathan Lyon at gully. Ben Stokes misjudged the bounce and failed to get the elevation on that. England are now 5 down.
Commentary.Howout: c Nathan Lyon b Cameron Green

Commentary.Commentary: Outside off, on a length. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Turning it into Jonny, quicker through the air. Jonny Bairstow tucks it to the short fine leg fielder.
Fuller length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow flicks to mid-wicket.
Flatter, quicker on off. Jonny Bairstow hangs back defends it out.
Flatter, on middle. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards mid on. No run there.
On middle this time, fuller. Jonny Bairstow taps it towards square leg.
Outside off, quicker through the air. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out off the back foot.
A short ball, now, on middle. Stokes sits under it.
On middle. Stokes shuffles and looks to defend but it takes the outside edge to point.
A full ball, slanting outside off. Ben Stokes is tempted as he tries to drive but fails to get any bat on it.
A length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes steps across and leaves it alone.
Outside off ball, left alone.
A length ball, outside off. Stokes covers his stumps and lets it through.
A loopy ball, on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
On middle, Blocked out.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Jonny Bairstow sweeps it to square leg for a single. The ball ricochets of the short leg fielder.
Short ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow defends it to short leg.
Flighted ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it on the deck.
Short and outside off, pushed down to long off for a single.
This one nips back in, on middle. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.
Short again, this time to Bairstow who ducks under it.
Length and on middle. Stokes steps across and flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Stokes punches it to point.
A length ball, outside off. Stokes looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short and on middle. Stokes sits under it.
Slower one, full and on off. Stokes skips down and tucks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Stokes prods to block it out.
Another solid defense from Ben Stokes.
Flatter and on middle. Blocked out.
On middle, drilled down to long on for a single.
Full and outside off. Jonny Bairstow puts a big stride forward and looks to sweep but misses. The ball lobs and goes to the first slip. Australia appeal but not given.
Touch fuller, on middle. Stokes defends it to mid on.
Length and outside off. Stokes leaves it alone.
A short ball, outside off. Ben Stokes arcs back and looks to ramp it away but misses.
Length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes shuffles and covers his stumps. Left alone.
Full and way outside off. Left alone.
Leg bye! Length ball, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. A leg bye taken as it rolls to fine leg.

Drinks! These two have done really well after losing Joe Root to steady the ship. Australia are still on the front foot and will look to take wickets at regular intervals. Also, Cameron Green to bowl now.
Full and on the pads. Ben Stokes nudges it towards short leg. Dot to end the over.
Full in length, outside the off pole. This time Stokes goes on the back foot and defends it out.
Loopy delivery, on middle. Ben Stokes blocks it solidly.
SIX! Bang! That's the Stokes we know! Nathan Lyon serves a loopy ball, full in length, around middle. Ben Stokes shimmies down the track and tonks it over long on over a biggie.
Outside off. Blocked out.
A tossed up ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow prods forward and uses his wrists perfectly and works it away towards deep mid-wicket for three runs.
Another fuller length delivery, outside off. Ben Stokes shuffles across and dabs it towards point.
Overpitches it, outside off. Ben Stokes lunges and pushes it towards mid off.

FOUR! Sweet touch! Mitchell Starc serves a length ball, down the leg. Ben Stokes just flicks it with the perfect timing all the way towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. 100 up for England as well.
Fuller, outside off. Ben Stokes leans forward and blocks it out.

Short of a length, outside the off pole. Jonny Bairstow looks to guide this one on the off side but gets a thick inside edge, just away from the leg stump and all the way towards fine leg. One run taken.
Overpitched, around the fourth stump line. Jonny Bairstow offers no shot on that.
Shorter, outside off. Ben Stokes stands tall and defends that one.
An off-break, around the pads. Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards mid on for a single.
Turning it into the right-hander, much quicker this time, on middle. Jonny Bairstow blocks out off the back foot.
Slower through the air again, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it to cover.
Loopy delivery again, outside off. Jonny Bairstow lunges and pushes it back to the bowler.
Tosses it up, outside off. Jonny Bairstow with a solid front foot defense.
Nathan Lyon (5-2-6-0) is back into the attack.
Mitchell Starc delivers a good-length ball, on the pads again. Jonny Bairstow hangs back and tucks it towards fine leg. A single taken and Jonny Bairstow will keep strike for the next over.
Tad shorter this time, outside off. Jonny Bairstow shoulders arms.
On a length, drifting it on the pads. Jonny blocks it out.
Tad fuller, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow taps it to mid-wicket. No run there.
Short of a length, wide of off. Jonny Bairstow, on back foot, slashes it over point for a couple of runs.

Nicely driven! Starc overpitches it, outside off. Stokes drives it one-handedly through the covers. Marnus Labuschagne chases it all the way towards the boundary, puts in a dive, and keeps the ball away from the boundary ropes. Three runs taken.
Length, around middle, Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
A good-length ball, on the pads, angling it into the right-hander. Jonny looks to defend that but misses and gets hit high on the pads. No run there.
Length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes shuffles across while walking down the pitch and taps it to mid on for a quick single.
Going around the wicket, serves a length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes offers no shot.
Fuller again, around middle. Jonny Bairstow works it away wide of mid on and scampers through to the other end.
Full in length, angling it into the pads. Jonny Bairstow tucks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Boundary to end the over! Short of a length, on middle. Stokes stays back and pulls it to the fine leg fence. Welcome boundary.
A length ball, on middle. Stokes rocks back and blocks it to mid on.
Angles it on the pads, worked to mid-wicket.
On a length, on the pads, this is flicked to the fine leg region. Jonny Bairstow is off the mark.
Length and on off. Bairstow defends it in front of him.
A length ball, outside off. Bairstow leaves it alone.
Again charges down the track and steers it to point. Maiden over.
Length and on off. Stokes steps across and nudges it on the leg side.
A length ball, on off. Stokes steps forward and blocks it on the deck.
Fuller ball, outside off, pushed to mid off.
Again shuffles and skips down, Stokes tucks it away to mid-wicket.
On a length, around off. Ben Stokes continues to be busy as he comes down the track to defend it out but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW but nothing given.
Jonny Bairstow comes to the crease now.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Who said Starc is injured! Here he is with the wicket of the big fish! Root perishes just after his fifty and England in a spot of trouble now. A length ball, slanting outside off. Just like the previous delivery, Root goes for the drive but this time he gets a thick outside edge to the keeper. Alex Carey behind the sticks dives to his right and takes a sharp catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: A full ball, outside off. Root drives it off the inner half of the bat to mid on.
A yorker now, outside off. Root jams it out to backward point.
A length ball, on middle. Root defends it off the front foot.
Length again, outside off. Root taps it to the gully region.
A length ball, on middle. Root taps it to point.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
An appeal for LBW but not given. A length ball, around off. Stokes skips down and looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Might be missing the wickets.
FIFTY for Joe Root, the skipper has risen to the occasion but even he knows the job is not yet completed. Now slants a full ball, on the pads, this is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Root hops and taps it to point.
A length ball, on off. kept out.
Beautiful delivery! A length ball, outside off, the ball just straightens up off the deck. Root looks to defend inside the line but misses.
Fuller ball, on off. Stokes prods and blocks it out.
Again down the leg side. Stokes shuffles across and misses his flick. Stokes has been busy in his crease since he came on.
Fuller ball, on off. Defended out.
A full ball, down the leg side. Stokes looks to flick but misses it. There was a noice on its way and there was a slight appeal for caught behind. Was off the pads though.
Full and on off, pushed to the left of mid off for a single.
A full ball, outside off. Stokes punches it wide of mid off and takes three runs before the fielder cuts it off.
Overpitches it this time, outside off. Joe Root carves it towards point. The ball does not race away to the boundary, but the batters pick up two runs.
Pulls his length back, outside off again. Joe Root pushes it to covers. No run there.
Full-length again, outside off. Root lunges and defends it out.
Fuller, outside off. Root offers no shot on that.

FOUR! Another four! Edgy boundary this time. Scott Boland serves a length ball, outside off. Joe Root looks to defend that but manages to get a thick outside edge past the diving gully for a boundary.
FOUR! Top shot by Joe Root! A back of a length, outside off. Joe Root waits back, and chops that beautifully past point for a boundary.
Swinging it away, full and outside off. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Short in length, on the body. Ben Stokes tucks it to fine leg.

Mitchell Starc changes his length this time, goes full on this occasion, around off. Joe Root punches that past mid-off. Mid-off does put in a dive to stop that, but can't get hold of it. Three runs taken.
Back of a length, at 138.2 clicks, outside the off stump. Joe Root will let that sail to the keeper.
Mitchell Starc serves a length ball this time, on middle. Joe Root gets an outside edge towards gully.
Short in length, outside the off pole. Joe Root hangs back and defends it out.
Speculations were there about Starc been injured while fielding but here he is ready to steam in.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Joe Root taps it with the inner half of his bat towards fine leg. Single to end the over.
On a length, on the pads. Stokes tucks it towards square leg. A single taken.
Fuller this time, wide of off. Ben Stokes offers no shot on that one.
Back of a length, around middle. Ben Stokes walks down the crease and is surprised with the extra bounce as the ball hits his gloves and rolls towards the off side.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes shoulders arms.
Slight halt in play as a plastic bag is flying around and they wait to wash it away. Ready to resume.
Scott Boland delivers a full-length ball, around middle. Joe Root leans forward and looks to defend, but gets a thick inside edge towards third man for a single.
Who will bowl from the other end? It is Scott Boland.
Tad fuller, on middle. Ben Stokes blocks it solidly.
Beaten! Cummins with a shorter delivery, outside off. Ben Stokes looks to defend but gets beaten by the extra bounce. The ball zips past through the outside edge.
Length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes walks down the pitch and leaves it alone.
We are back for the post-lunch session. Ben Stokes joins Joe Root in the middle. All smiles in Australia's camp as they stride out. Pat Cummins will complete his over.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

Not the start England would have desired, it's been a disappointing session for them. The openers, Haseeb Hameed and Zak Crawley failed to build an innings and were dismissed early in the session. Joe Root and Dawid Malan took things under control and tried to rebuild the innings. They did some repair work, but could not hold on till the end of the session as Malan was dismissed just before lunch. Joe Root is still standing tall at the crease, he looks in good touch and will have to stick around till the end and guide his side to a good total. Will the Australian bowlers continue to cause trouble? Or will England build another partnership? Do join us in a short while to find out. Another exciting session awaits.

The Hosts are on top yet again. It was Pat Cummins who drew the first blood in his first over of the game. He soon picked up the wicket of Zak Crawley as well and put England in trouble early in the session. Joe Root and Dawid Malan tried doing some damage control and put together a solid partnership. But, it was none other than Pat Cummins who broke the partnership and ended Dawid Malan's resilience. It's the captain leading by example. They will be mighty pleased with this session.

Different Test, same story. Australia's dominance continues and England are in trouble yet again. It's been a solid session of Test cricket, with the Hosts leading from the front. The wicket of Dawid Malan at the stroke of Lunch has put more pressure on Root now.

OUT! TAKEN! This was coming, with the way Pat Cummins was bowling with discipline lines and lengths. Malan was struggling and his stay has been short cut just at the stroke of lunch break. This was on a length, slanting outside off, Malan stays back and looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge to the first slip where David Warner takes a sharp catch. Body blow for England. That will also be Lunch on Day 1.
Commentary.Howout: c David Warner b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: On a length, angling on middle, extra pace here. Root rocks back and clips it to deep square leg for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Root chases this wayward delivery and has a poke at it, misses.
Flatter and on off. Malan punches off the back foot to covers.
Short ball, outside off. Root steers it past short third man for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off. Joe Root gets on the front foot to defend this out.
Flatter and on off. Blocked out.
A flighted ball, on off, tucked away to square leg.
A full ball, on off, driven to covers.
On a length, outside off. Malan shoulders arms to it.

EDGED! A full ball, outside off, seams back in. Malan looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge, just short of the first slip. A wicket at the course of lunch break would do wonders for Australia.
Short ball, outside off. Root rides it as he pulls it with soft hands to deep square leg for a single.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
A length ball, outside off, nips back in off the deck. Root shoulders arms to it.
Good fielding! A full ball, outside off. Root drives it nicely but the fielder at covers dives to his right to stop it.
A loopy ball, on off Root pushes it through point for a single.
Darted on the pads, this is flicked through square leg for a couple of runs.
Flatter, quicker and on middle. Root rocks back and tucks it to square leg for a single.
A full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Slightly short on middle. Root gets on the back foot as he defends it.
A tossed up ball, on off. Root prods and looks to flick but gets a soft leading edge to mid off.
Now Malan hits it off the middle and drives it nicely but straight to mid off.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller delivery, outside off. Malan gets one hand off as he drives this through covers. Not quite off the middle and two runs are taken.
Length again, outside off. Malan leaves it alone to the keeper.
Now serves a length ball, outside off. Left alone.
A short ball from Cummins, on off. Malan sways away from it.
On middle. Root hits it to the right of the bowler and Lyon dives to save some runs for his team.
Tossesiy up, on off. Root defends it on the off side.
Flatter and on middle, Malan turns it to square leg for a single.
Angles a full ball, on middle. Malan defends it solidly.
On middle. Root skips down and tucks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Sharp turn from Lyon, this one lands on off and turns back in. Blocked out.
Around off, on a length, Root gets an inside edge to square leg for a single. Good over for England, 9 coming off the over.
Short of a length, on the hips, this is flicked to square leg for a single. The repay shows Starc catching his back right after the throw.
Quick run! A length ball, on off. Root taps it in front of covers and takes a quick single.
Full again, on off. Malan now drives it through mid off for three runs. Good running.
A length ball, on the pads. Malan flicks it to square leg.
A full ball, outside off. Root drives it nicely through mid off for three runs.
Pat Cummins is back into the attack.
Short and outside off, cut away to point.
This was much quicker, on middle. Malan punches off the back foot to the bowler.
Touch fuller, on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle. Kept out.
A tossed up ball, on off. Malan skips down and looks to counter-attack budgets hit on the pads. A muted appeal follows for LBW.
A full ball, angling on the pads. Malan blocks it on the leg side.
Back-of-a-length delivery, around off. Joe Root blocks it out.
Overpitching it, around middle. Root works it away towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.

Good stop! Cameron Green serves a fuller ball, outside off. Dawid Malan leans forward and drives it towards backward point. Nathan Lyon dives to this left and makes an amazing stop there. Saved three runs there.
LEG BYE! Length ball, drifting it onto the pads. Joe Root looks to flick but misses and the ball hits the pads and rolls square on the leg side. Leg bye taken.
Back of a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Short of a length, around the pads. Joe Root works it away towards mid-wicket.
Darting it on the pads this time, short in length. Dawid Malan, on back foot, taps it mid-wicket.
Tad shorter, outside off. Malan chops it to point off his back foot.
Fuller, flighting it again, and turning it away from the left-hander. Malan leaves it alone.
Tossing it up again, around middle. Malan taps it to short leg. No run there.
Loopy delivery, on middle. Dawid Malan leans forwards and defends it out solidly.
Nathan Lyon starts off with a flighted delivery, outside off. Dawid Malan lets that go.
Nathan Lyon is into the attack now.
Short delivery, outside off. Joe Root stands tall and punches it off his back foot towards covers for a brace.
Back of a length, on the body. Joe Root blocks it out.
Change of line this time, serves a full-length delivery, on the pads. Joe Root flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Overpitching it again, around the off pole. Joe Root lunges and pushes it back to the bowler.
Full in length again, on middle. Root leans forward and blocks it towards mid on.
Fuller, down the leg, at 135.1 clicks. Joe Root looks to flicks but that's out of his reach. The ball will flow to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. Dawid Malan shoulders arms.
Pacey delivery, touch fuller, outside off. Dawid Malan manages to get an outside edge towards Cameron Green at gully. He does well there to stop the ball.
Maintains the same length, serves a good-length ball, outside off. Dawid Malan taps it to mid-wicket. No run there.
A length ball, on middle. Dawid Malan defends it solidly.
Tad shorter, around the off pole. Dawid Malan, on back foot, defends it on the off side.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Dawid Malan blocks it watchfully.
Angles it on the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single.
Whizzed past the outside edge. Seam movement there, just around off. Malan lunges and tries to defend but misses it.
Now gets back to the good-length. Malan comes forward and defends it out.
Short ball, might be the first one we have seen from the start. Malan sways away from the line of the ball.
A length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Serves it from around the wicket, way outside off. Malan lets it through to the keeper.
A length ball, on off. Root blocks it back to the bowler as Boland gets low and grabs it.
A length ball, on off. Root works it to mid off and tries for a cheeky single but opts not to take it.
Fuller ball, on off. Root blocks it back on the surface. Scott Boland is making the batter play rather than bowling it way outside off. Good from the debutant.
Now hops and defends this length ball back on the deck.
Length and on off. Root blocks it off the back foot to covers.
FOUR! Through the gap! A length ball, outside off. Root defends with an angled bat and the ball rolls through the slip cordon for a boundary.

DRINKS! Australia on top yet again! Pat Cummins has sent both the England openers back to the hut early. Joe Root and Dawid Malan are out there in the middle doing some damage control. Can the two batters survive till lunch? We shall know soon. Also, Scott Boland is back into the attack.
On middle, on a length. Defended out.
Easy leave from Malan as this is way outside off. Need to bowl in the 4th stump line to make an impact here.
Now extra bounce here from Green. Malan gets on his toes and defends it to point.
136 clicks from Green. Outside off. Left alone.
Another length ball, outside off. Malan shoulders arms to it.
Starts from around the wicket, outside off. Malan leaves it alone.
Cameron Green comes into the attack now.
Cummins finishes with a pacy delivery. This is on a length and outside off. Root looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge to the keeper.
Sharp work from Cameron Green! A length ball, outside off. Root looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge to Green who collects it on a bounce.
A length ball, outside off. Root hits it to point.
A length ball, angling on middle. Root flicks it to deep square leg for a couple now. Joe Root scoring at a much brisk pace here.
A length ball, outside off. Root defends it t towards covers.
Touch fuller, on off. Root shuffles across a bit and taps it to point.
A length ball, on off. Malan blocks it out.
FOUR! 18 deliveries and Dawid Malan is off the mark. A length ball, outside off. Malan looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge in between the slip cordon and the gully fielder for a boundary.
On a length, on middle. Root nudges it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Length again, on off. Root blocks it to covers now and shouts 'No run' to his partner.
On a length, on off, defended to point.
A length ball, on middle. Root flicks it more off the inside portion of the bat to square leg for a brace.
Good-length, outside off. Dawid Malan taps it to cover. He was looking for a quick single but was sent back in time by Root. The fielder at cover was quick to grab the ball and throw it.
Full in length, wide of off. Dawid Malan shoulders arms on that one too.
Tad fuller, outside off, shaping it into the left-hander. Dawid Malan leaves that alone.
Change of length this time, serves a full-length delivery, around the pads. Joe Root uses his wrists and flicks it past mid-wicket. Three runs taken.
Beaten! Pat Cummins delivers a length ball again, around the fourth stump. Joe Root looks to defend but gets beaten as the ball zips through the outside edge.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Joe Root offers no shot on that one.
Change of angle to the left-hander, goes around the wicket, length ball, outside off. Malan defends it out solidly.
Full in length, outside off. Joe Root lunges and pushes it toward cover for a single.
Touch fuller this time, shaping it back in again. Joe Root looks to flick but gets an inside edge towards short leg.
And again! Good-length ball, nipping back in. Root gets beaten again. He looks to block it out but gets hit on his knee roll.
Much better from Scott Boland. A length ball, shaping back in on middle. Joe Root looks to defend but gets hit on his pads.
FOUR! First boundary for England! Beautiful shot by Joe Root. Overpitches this one, on the pads. Joe Root leans forwards and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Touch shorter, outside off. Dawid Malan shoulders arms. End of a successful over by the Australian skipper.
Outside off again, length ball. Dawid Malan blocks it out.
Going round the wicket to the left-hander, serves a full ball, outside off. Dawid Malan leans and defends that one.
Quick single and Joe Root is off the mark! A length ball, on middle. Root tucks it to mid-wicket and takes off for a quick single. Was a little risky but he makes his ground on time.

The skipper, Joe Root walks out to the middle. Meanwhile, Dawid Malan has gone back to the pavilion with a quick run. Not sure why though, might be nature's call. He is back and we are ready to continue.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Pat Cummins strikes again and Zak Crawley walks back. What a start by Australia! A length ball, on middle, getting some extra bounce on this occasion. Zak Crawley looks to block this out but gets a thick outside edge to Cameron Green at gully who takes a good low catch. England are now 2 down and yet again the openers have failed to rise to the occasion.
Commentary.Howout: c Cameron Green b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: On a length, around off at 137.8 clicks. Zak Crawley defends, but gets an inside edge back to his pads.
Good end to Scott Boland's first over! Good-length, around middle. Dawid Malan defends it out.

Quick single there! Direct hit could have been curtains for Zak Crawley. A length ball, outside off. Zak Crawley taps it towards cover and scampers through to the other end. Nathan Lyon collects the ball and has shy at the bowler's end, but misses.
Overpitching it again, outside off. Zak Crawley goes for the drive but gets an inside edge towards mid on. Could not capitalize on this one.
Maintains the same length, full around middle. Zak Crawley defends it watchfully.
Fuller in length, around middle and off at 136.8 clicks. Zak Crawley blocks it towards mid on.
Scott Boland begins with a length ball, outside off, Zak Crawley lets that go through.
Here comes the debutant, Scott Boland as he replaces Mitchell Starc.
Good finish by Cummins. Touch fuller, around off. Malan leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, on the pads. Dawid Malan blocks it out.
Zak Crawley showing some positive intent here! Good timing on that. A full-length delivery again, on middle. Zak Crawley tucks it past mid-wicket. Three runs taken.
Pat Cummins serves a fuller delivery, on off. Zak Crawley defends it out solidly.
On a length this time, on the pads. Zak Crawley blocks it out watchfully. There is a misfield at mid on by Scott Boland but no runs are taken.
Full-length, around off. Zak Crawley leans forward and drives it through covers for a brace.
In the air but safe! A length ball, on middle. Zak Crawley is early as he looks to flick but gets a leading edge and the ball drops safe at the point region. Three taken.
On a length, outside off. Zak Crawley with an easy leave.
On a length, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone. These two need to get used to the pitch and give a good start to England.
Outside off again, Left alone.
Much better line from Starc. This can make the batters go for it and can nick them. A length ball, just around off. Zak Crawley leaves it very late.
A full ball, angling outside off. Crawley lets it through to the keeper.
Pat Cummins making the ball move. Really, a good start from Australia. On a length, outside off. Left alone.
This one shapes back in and only the extra bounce has saved Malan here as he tries to leave but gets hit on the pads.
Touch fuller, just around off. Probing lines and lengths from Pat Cummins. Malan leaves it alone.
Short of a length, outside off. Malan shoulders arms to it.
Sheer pace from Cummins. A length ball, way down the leg side. Malan looks to flick but misses and the keeper takes it across.
On a length, on the pads. Malan defends it to short leg.
Maiden over! Fuller ball, outside off. Crawley leaves it untouch.
SWING AND A MISS! This was full and outside off. Crawley looks for a big booming drive but fails to get any bat on it.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
This one flew through to the keeper. Good carry from Alex Carey. A length ball, in the channel of uncertainty.  Zak Crawley is on his toes as he lets it through.
Another outside off delivery and another leave from Zak Crawley.
A length ball, outside off. Zak Crawley shoulders arms.
Brilliant over from Pat Cummins! Short of a length, slanting outside off. Malan looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Dawid Malan comes in at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Pat Cummins comes back in the side and strikes straightaway. Haseeb Hameed goes back with a duck and openers continues to struggle against Australia. This was full and just around off. Haseeb Hameed is tentative as he leans to drive but it takes the outside edge and goes to Alex Carey, behind the sticks who pouches it comfortably. Australia are up and running on the Boxing Day.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
This one comes back in off the deck. The length was a bit short and hits Haseeb Hameed high on the pds. Good bowling from Cummins.
Zak Crawley is underway. Confident punch from Crawley. A full ball, on middle. Zak Crawley shows the full face of the bat and punches it wide of mid on for three runs.
A length ball, outside off. Crawley leaves it alone.
Pat Cummins will bowl from the other end.
This one shapes back in and whizzes past the off pole. Haseeb Hameed again leaves it alone to the keeper.
Nice line from Starc. He serves it just around off. Hameed shoulders arms to it. Much better length.
This is way outside off. Hameed lets it through without any trouble.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Again comes around the wicket. Starc is trying to find some pace and create an angle. A length ball, outside off. Hameed leaves it alone to the keeper.
Now comes over the wicket and bowls a length ball, outside off. Left alone by Hameed.
Starc starts with a length ball, slanting outside off. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to it. Not a good start from Starc as it is called a no ball for overstepping.

We are done with all the pre-match formalities and now it is time for the action. The players of Australia stride out to the middle. Haseeb Hameed and Zak Crawley are the openers for England. Mitchell Starc has the new ball. Here we go...

Joe Root, the skipper of England, says that they would have bowled first as well. Says that the first hour is always crucial and hopes to start well. Adds that he expects a reaction from his players and it is a great opportunity to do so.

Pat Cummins, the skipper of Australia, says that it was tough to sit on the couch at home but he thought Smith led the team very well. Adds that they will bowl, as there is some good grass coverage on the surface. Mentions that they are very lucky to have Scott Boland by their side, he is a fantastic player.

England (Playing XI) - Haseeb Hameed, Zak Crawley (In place of Rory Burns), Dawid Malan, Joe Root (C), Ben Stokes, Jonny Bairstow (In place of Ollie Pope), Jos Buttler (WK), Mark Wood (In place of Chris Woakes), Ollie Robinson, Jack Leach (In place of Stuart Broad), James Anderson.

Australia (Playing XI) - David Warner, Marcus Harris, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Travis Head, Cameron Green, Alex Carey (WK), Pat Cummins (C) (In place of Jhye Richardson), Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Scott Boland (On Debut) (In place of Michael Neser).
TOSS - The coin goes up and lands in favour of Australia. They have elected to BOWL first.

UPDATE 10.17 am Local Time (11.17 pm GMT, previous day) - We have an official update. The toss will take place at 10.30 am local time (11.30 pm GMT, previous day). And the match will start at 11.00 am local time (12.00 am GMT). Unless there are no more interruptions.

UPDATE 10.07 am Local Time (11.07 pm GMT, previous day) - We have some positive news and thankfully we didn't have to wait for long. The covers are coming off and the umpires are out to have a look. The forecast cautioned for a very small delay and after that, the weather looks pretty clear for the rest of the day.

UPDATE 9.55 am Local Time (10.55 pm GMT, previous day) - Not the start we were looking for to the Boxing Day Test but the TOSS HAS BEEN DELAYED due to rain. It is not that heavy but it is drizzling all around. Let us hope we get some positive news soon. Stay tuned.

The Host are in a pretty comfortable position but they made some changes as well. Scott Boland is handed the Baggy Green and is all set to make his Test debut. While Pat Cummins is back to lead his team. England have a mountain to climb and this match needs their players to be more competitive and aggressive to keep their hopes of winning the Ashes alive. The Boxing Day Test has always given us some remarkable events and surely more memories will be made again. Stay tuned for the toss and other updates.

England have already declared their playing XI and they have made a flurry of changes. Rory Burns had enough chances to repair his form but now the opening task is handed to Zak Crawley. While Jonny Bairstow gives more senior presents to the side as he replaces the young, Ollie Pope, While Mark Wood and Jack Leach find a place for themselves as well.

Hello and a warm welcome to all! It is time for the Boxing Day Test. Australia are 2-0 up in the five-match Test series and if you look it closely, they have not just won the match but even session by session they are beating England comprehensively. A do or die situation for England, a draw at least is required here to keep the series alive.
... Day 1, Session 1 ...

ENGLAND ATTEMPT A REJIG - This was always seeming inevitable. And this has happened not just because England are 0-2 down. The prelude has been their batting issues against India, both home and away and as a result, the visitors have made FOUR CHANGES to their playing XI from Adelaide. Rory Burns, Ollie Pope, Stuart Broad and Chris Woakes have been dropped and their replacements would be Zak Crawley, Jonny Bairstow, Mark Wood and Jack Leach. Is this the sign for the future? It is unimaginable not to see the Anderson-Broad combination on the field if both are fit and while one understands the need for spin and extra pace in Leach and Wood, the dropping of both, Broad and Woakes comes as a surprise. One assumes that Ollie Robinson is simply out of contention to be left out, unless he is tired or having a niggle and the toss up would have been between Anderson and Broad to accomodate Wood. England's XI - Haseeb Hameed, Zak Crawley, Dawid Malan, Joe Root (c), Ben Stokes, Jonny Bairstow, Jos Buttler (wk), Mark Wood, Ollie Robinson, Jack Leach and James Anderson.

A SHOCKING CHRISTMAS PRESENT? Australia have announced that SCOTT BOLAND will make his Ashes debut, with regular skipper Pat Cummins returning. Jhye Richardson and Michael Neser would be the unlucky ones missing out. The rest of the playing XI would be the same, given that Josh Hazlewood has not recovered yet. Australian XI - David Warner, Marcus Harris, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Travis Head, Cameron Green, Alex Carey (wk), Pat Cummins (c), Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon and Scott Boland (DEBUT).

The players are back on the field. Cummins has his team in a huddle. The conditions are slightly overcast and the home side will hope for some good swing movement. Out come the English openers - Haseeb Hameed and Zak Crawley and the players disperse. Mitchell Starc has the new ball in his hand. Who will take first strike? It will be Hameed. Here we go then...
... THIRD INNINGS ...

Right then. Around 16 overs to go for Stumps, with nearly an hour left. Don't think we will get all of those in but Australia would dearly love 2-3 wickets. England, on the other hand, need a wicketless passage of play, for a better tomorrow. Stay tuned.

Having said all of the below, Australia may not be too disappointed either. Yes, they would have wished to get to 350 at least and put up a lead of 200 but this deck suggests that batting is not easy at all. And if you look at the average third innings score at the MCG in the last 10 Tests, it is 182. If Australia can manage to live up to that stat, they will still be in a good position in this game. Almost everyone struggled, with only local lad Marcus Harris getting past 50. However, 45 runs came in total from the bats of Cummins and Starc, which could prove decisive in the end.

Plenty of grass on the pitch and it did not take long for the English bowlers to exploit it. Anderson struck the right chord pretty early and it has been England all through the day, except maybe for a brief period in between, after Lunch. Jimmy finished with a 4-fer while Robinson and Wood snared 2 apiece.

Is the glass half full or half empty? Depends on your point of view. Australia 76/1. 267 all out. Tremendous fightback from England. Australia 219/8. 267 all out. Excellent rearguard action from the hosts. So overall, the tourists would be very happy but if there is a term called momentum in cricket, it is with the hosts right now.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! And England finally bowl out Australia. The lead stops at 82. A length ball, outside off, Scott Boland stays inside the line and looks to slice it through the off side. But the extra pace defeats him and he is late into the shot. The outside edge is taken and Zak Crawley takes a nice catch at second slip. AUSTRALIA BOWLED OUT FOR 267!
Commentary.Howout: c Zak Crawley b Mark Wood

Commentary.Commentary: Short in length, outside off. Scott Boland offers no shot on that.
Fuller this time, outside off. Mitchell Starc drives and gets an outside edge towards deep point for a single.
Adding some handy runs here these two! Short of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc chops it through backward point for two runs.
Mark Wood serves a full-length delivery, on the pads. Scott Boland uses his wrists and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket. Three runs taken.

DRINKS BREAK. Well, quite a few people are awaiting that final wicket. This could be the last time Jimmy will be touring Australia. Imagine a 5-fer at the MCG, in his last outing. Think about the English openers. They have been waiting for perhaps 10-12 overs now. Right from the time Carey fell. Australia have swelled their lead to 76, thanks to once again, some lower-order rearguard action. Here's Mark Wood after Drinks. 19-2-65-1 so far.
Fuller, outside off. Mitchell Starc drives it straight to the fielder at cover.
On a good-length, around off. Mitchell Starc presses forward and looks to defend that gets a slight inside edge towards mid-wicket.
Shortish delivery, on the thigh pad. Scott Boland flicks it away towards square leg for a single.

The MCG roars! Oh... how much do they love their lads...Full, outside off, Scott Boland lunges, opens the face of his bat and guides it behind point, for his first runs in Test cricket! The crowd almost gives a standing ovation! Two runs taken.
Beaten! A peach of a delivery, A full ball, just outside off. Scott Boland goes for the drive but gets beaten as the ball nips away a tad bit.
Full in length, around off. Mitchell Starc pushes it down towards long on for a single.
On length, outside off. Scott Boland leaves that alone.
Short delivery, Starc swivels across and pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.

LEG BYE! An LBW shout but the umpire signals a leg bye. A full delivery, drifting onto the pads. Scott Boland misses his flick and gets rapped on the pads. A shout for LBW but umpire thinks otherwise. The batters steal a leg bye in return.
Back of a length, around the off pole. Mitchell Starc guides it towards third man and rotates the strike.
Short of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc looks to play that but gets beaten by the lack of pace.
Tad slower this time, outside off. Mitchell Starc shoulders arms to it.
Great to see Ollie Robinson back fit as he is ready to bowl now.
Yes, he does! This was on a length and way outside off. Boland offers no shot to it.
On a length, on off. Boland blocks it towards cover. Can he survive this over?
A length ball, outside off. Scott Boland leaves it alone to the keeper.
Short of a length, on middle. Starc stands tall and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Debutant and local lad, Scott Boland, walks out at number 11.

OUT! CAUGHT! The quickfire stand is broken. 34 in 53 balls. A length ball, outside off, Pat Cummins backs away and swings like there is no tomorrow. But there is lack of pace on the ball, which means the shot is played in July, while the ball arrives in the month of December. A top edge is induced and Haseeb Hameed takes the simplest of catches at backward point. Decent knock by the skipper. Australia lead by 68.
Commentary.Howout: c Haseeb Hameed b James Anderson

Commentary.Commentary: Touch fuller, on off, pushed to mid on.

FOUR! TONK! 250 UP FOR AUSTRALIA! The lead has now swelled to 65, 34 of which, have come in this 9th-wicket stand! A short ball, around off, angling away, Mitchell Starc gets on top of the bounce and pulls it audaciously over mid-wicket!
On middle. Starc again gets lucky as he hits it off the slice through covers and another couple of runs are added to Australia's lead.
Valuable runs! A length ball, on off. Starc looks to go straight but it takes the splice and goes through point for a couple.
A length ball, outside off. Starc shoulders arms to it.

Oh dear. Robinson is not looking good. He comes running in but cannot complete the ball. He looks at his captain and... ROBINSON WALKS OFF. England are a bowler down now. It is Mr. 'Call-me-anytime' to finish Ollie's pending over. Here's Ben Stokes. 10-1-39-1 so far. He has to bat, he has to bowl, he has to captain when Root is off the field and now, he has to complete others' pending overs. Keeping is the only thing left now.

DROPPED! Toughie, toughie for Robinson and dear me, what do we see next? ROBINSON IS CATCHING HIS HAMSTRING! No, England do not need this. Coming to the ball, it was full and straight. Mitchell Starc did not need any second invitation and went straight back. However, the bat came before the ball could arrive. The ball took the inner half of the bat and went towards Robinson. But the bowler seemed to react a bit too soon. He felt the ball would come quicker but it came on slower than his anticipation. As a result, he was surprised and could not quite take it in the first attempt. Tried to do it in the second but then, the spikes on his shoes gave away and he slipped, with the ball slipping out too. And that, affected his hamstring too.
A length ball, on off. Starc punches it to covers.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Another swing and a miss! A full ball, outside off. Cummins looks for a big booming drive but fails to get any bat on it.
A length ball, outside off. Cummins works it to point.
On a length, on off, Cummins chops it to point. He wanted a single but was sent back.
Full ball, on off, pushed to covers.
BEATEN! A length ball, outside off. Pat Cummins drives it away from the body and misses it completely. Good bounce and carry. England will hope that the tail doesn't wag for a long time.
A length ball, outside off. Starc leaves it alone to the keeper.
Full ball, outside off. Starc drives it nicely but straight to covers.

DROPPED! James Anderson almost pulls off a blinder! Honestly, it is harsh to call that a drop but if there is someone who can take stingers in this team, it is Jimmy. He has taken plenty of these in the past and would have hoped that this one stuck too. Full, around middle, Pat Cummins backed away and swung hard. The ball went off the inner half of the bat slightly wide of mid on. Anderson there, dived full stretch to his right and almost pulled it off, but unfortunately for him, the ball did not stick. A single taken.
Around off, this is pushed to point.
A length ball, on middle. Blocked out.
FOUR! Straight down the ground! A full ball, on middle. Cummins punches it past the bowler and down the ground for a boundary.
Anderson continues to bowl straight and on the stumps. Cummins flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, on middle. Cummins defends it out.
Length and on middle. Starc clips it to square leg for a single.
A length ball, on off. Starc defends it back on the deck.
On a length, outside off. Cummins punches it through point for a single.
Anderson starts from around the wicket, full ball and on middle. Starc whips it to deep square leg for a single.

80 overs done. The second new ball is now available. Will Root take it straightaway? No reason why he shouldn't. AND ENGLAND TAKE THE SECOND NEW BALL. James Anderson is back on. 19-9-24-3 so far. Changed ends though. He has bowled mostly from the other end in this Test so far.
Shortish in length again, outside off. Mitchell Starc makes room and drops it towards cover.
Short of a length, down the leg this time. Mitchell Starc misses his flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Angling it onto the pads, a length delivery. Pat Cummins nudges it towards mid-wicket and scampers through to the other end. Australia now leads by 50 runs.
Back of a length, outside off. Pat Cummins dabs it to backward point.
Drops it short again, on the body. Mitchell Starc gets an inside edge onto the body. The ball rolls towards short fine leg. A single taken.
On a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc, on back foot, goes for the push but gets beaten as the ball zips past through the outside edge.
Short ball, over middle. Mitchell Starc doesn't get hold of his pull shot but manages to get a single towards square leg.
On a length again, on the pads this time. Pat Cummins flicks it away to the right of mid-wicket for a single.
Nicely cut away! A length ball, outside off. Pat Cummins waits back, and chops it through covers. Two runs taken.
Good-length delivery, around middle and leg. Pat Cummins blocks it on the leg side.
Fuller in length, around middle. Pat Cummins pushes it back to the bowler.
Ben Stokes delivers a short ball, on middle. Mitchell Starc waits back and pulls it away towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Changes from both ends now. Ben Stokes is back into the attack. His figures (9-1-34-1)
Shortish delivery again, outside off. Mitchell Starc taps it to cover and scampers through to the other end.
Back of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc hangs back and looks to chop this away, but fails to get any bat on it.
Short of a length, around off. Mitchell Starc jumps and defends this one.
Mark Wood goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander, serves a shortish delivery, around middle. Mitchell Starc blocks it out solidly.
On a length, around off. Pat Cummins, on back foot, pushes it towards cover. A single taken.
Swing and a miss! Mark Wood serves a length ball, outside off. Pat Cummins swings his bat and gets beaten due to extra pace.

Good captaincy from Root. If there is anything tailenders care about, it is about their body. They do not want to get hit by opposition fast bowlers. Hence, they play away from the body and the stumps and usually get defeated by extra pace. Joe has sensed that and got back Mark Wood. 16-2-55-1 so far.
Tossing it up, around off. Mitchell Starc lunges and blocks it out.
Full and on middle. Pat Cummins whips it down to long on for a single.
Flatter and on off, pushed to covers.
FOUR! The skipper goes up and over! This was full and on off. Pat Cummins lifts it over mid off and wide of long on for a boundary.
Short ball, on the pads. Starc hangs on the back foot and tucks it to square leg for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Starc prods to defend.

Stokes nearly had two! A good length, outside off. Mitchell Starc strides forward and looks to drive this. But he is too early into his shot, and manages to get an outside edge towards gully. The ball flies and falls just short of Haseeb Hameed at gully.
Goes full on this occasion, around off. Mitchell Starc pushes it to mid on.
Back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Mitchell Starc leaves it alone.
Mitchell Starc walks in at number 10, replacing Carey.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Forget Patrick, England have got Alex! It is Mr. 'Make-It-Happen', Ben Stokes. The last of the recognized batter departs. Australia just ahead by 34. Full, outside off, Carey, who is in one-day mode, reaches out to drive. But with an upright body and the knee of the back leg not quite getting down, the weight of the body could not quite get transferred onto the feet. By the time that could happen, the ball is already through and the outside edge is taken. Simple catch for Carey's counterpart.
Commentary.Howout: c Jos Buttler b Ben Stokes

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller in length, around middle. Pat Cummins looks to defend but gets an inside edge towards fine leg. A single taken.

Full, on the pads, Alex Carey leans and flicks it past mid-wicket, to his right. It is a long boundary and the batsmen have enough time to come back for the third. And they do. But should they have? Seems like Carey is trusting Cummins to hang on here. England will not mind Patrick on strike.
Change. Ben Stokes is back into the attack. His figures till now read (8-1-29-0).
Very full and on off. Carey reverse-sweeps it through point for a single.
A  loopy delivery, on off. Carey defends it out.
Slightly short and outside off. Cummins hits it to point for a single.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Beautifully bowled! Tosses it up, gives some flight to it and lands it on middle. Pat Cummins tries to defend but gets an outside edge past first slip for a couple of runs.
Full and slanting on the pads, flicked to square leg.
Length and on off. Carey defends with his bat and pad together.
Short in length, outside off. Left alone.
Touch fuller, angling around off. Carey puts his front foot out and punches it wide of mid off for a couple of runs.
On middle, on a length, tucked away to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Lovely bowling from Ollie Robinson! On a length, outside off. Carey looks to push but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
A length ball, on middle. Carey is squared up as he looks to defend. Gets an outside edge wide of the diving third slip fielder and towards third man. Two taken.
Tosses it up, full and on middle. Cummins leans and pushes it to mid-wicket.
The captain, Pat Cummins, comes out now, at number 9. Will Carey farm the strike?

OUT! Green has been adjudged LBW! But he has taken this upstairs. This looks dead close. Nothing on the Hot Spot. Time for RTS. Nothing. Ball away from the bat. Now then... now then.... big moment for Leach... UMPIRE'S CALL ON WICKETS! Australia hold on to a review but lose Green. Big, big wicket for Leach. He came in from around the wicket and slid this with the arm, around middle and leg. Green went back to flick but missed and was hit on the pads. The English camp immediately went up in appeal and umpire Paul Reiffel, after thinking for a while, raised his finger. Hawk Eye showed the ball to be sliding down the leg side, but on its way, just clipping the leg stump! Umpire's call stays to raise boos from the crowd. Australia 7 down. Just 22 ahead. Just the second wicket for Leach in the series. Might be the one which keeps the Ashes alive.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Jack Leach

Commentary.Commentary: Flatter and on off. Green defends it off the front foot.
That was just away from kissing the edge! Quicker, flatter and around off. Green waits and looks to dab it away but misses.
Tossed up, on middle, Carey sweeps it to square leg for a single.
Short and on the pads. Carey flicks it with soft hands to leg slip who collects it on a bounce.
Jack Leach (12-0-35-0) will bowl from the other end.
Length and on middle, this is flicked to deep backward square leg for a single.
Tad fuller, on off, pushed through covers for a single.
A length ball, around off, this one nips back in. Green looks to defend but the ball goes through the gate and hits him high on the pads.
FOUR! Straight as an arrow! A full ball, on middle. Green shows the full face of the bat and punches it straight down the ground for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Green hangs back and blocks it out.
Ollie Robinson starts the session with a short ball, on middle. Green ducks under it.
We are back for the final session. Alex Carey and Cameron Green will resume their innings. Ollie Robinson to initiate this session. Also, the second new ball will be due in 9 overs.
... DAY 2, FINAL SESSION ...

Right. 16 wickets in 5 sessions! Did not feel that was coming. England will aim to knock over the lower order of Australia quickly here, and keep the lead under 50. The hosts, on the other hand, might start playing their shots a little bit. That does involve a bit of risk, but if a couple of shots come off, the bowlers might lose their rhythm a bit. Also, Root will be looking at the scoreboard and might start spreading the field a little bit. Either ways, we are in for some thrilling action after the break. The resumption will be at 4 pm local (0500 GMT).

There is a lot in this pitch and the England seamers are continuously exploiting those stuff. Anderson has been phenomenal while Robinson, Wood and Stokes have been tirelessly working over. Australia have found runs hard to come by. One of the commentators on air remembered a Sheffield Shield century here by Nic Maddinson earlier, after which, the player said that it was a pitch where you never felt settled. Even a batter batting in the 70s and 80s was uncomfortable, as Harris found out. If that is the case, any lead above 50 would be valuable.

This is what happens when you hold onto your catches. England have been in good positions in both the previous Tests but have let things slip. However, this time, because of the conditions, they have managed to squeeze the pressure on Australia and the result is that, for the first time in 3 matches, we have not seen a centurion from Australia. Leave alone a centurion, where are the partnerships? After the quickfire opening stand of 57, we have had just one 50-run stand, between Head and Harris and that was the time when England were letting the game drift.

Right. What an enthralling session. 69/2 in 29 overs. The Test is alive. The Ashes are alive! Really good game of cricket from both sides. England started the session listlessly but then bounced back. However, with the pressure mounting, the Aussies have shown a little bit of urgency in the last 30 minutes or so.

Two taken! This was full and outside off. Carey sweeps it well and towards fine leg and scampers across for a couple of runs. Carey puts in a dive as the fielder has a shy at the keeper's end. That will also be Tea on Day 2.
Carey reverse-sweeps this full ball through point and collects a couple of runs.
Flatter and on off. Carey nudges it to mid-wicket.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Tosses it up, on middle. Alex Carey now attempts the reverse-sweep and hits it well but Mark Wood puts in a dive at point and stops it.
Full and way outside off. Carey tries to drag it from outside off as he looks to sweep but misses.
Jack Leach (11-0-31-0) is back into the attack.
On length, outside off. Cameron Green drives it towards cover.
Back of a length, outside off. Cameron Green jumps and taps it towards point.
Change of length this time, goes full, outside off. Cameron Green leans forward and blocks it out.
Another bouncer, around middle. Cameron Green ducks under it.
Short again, on middle. Carey tucks it towards fine leg. A single taken.
A short ball, on the body. Alex Carey takes his eyes off this pacey delivery and gets hit on the bicep.
Puling his length back, darting it on the pads. Alex Carey pushes it towards fine leg. A single taken.
Very full, on middle. Alex Carey taps it to mid-wicket.
On a length, on the pads. Alex Carey tucks it away towards fine leg for two runs.
Tad shorter, darting it on the pads. Alex Carey misses his flick as the ball nips back in a tad.
A full-length delivery, on the pads. Alex Carey flicks it towards mid-wicket.
On a length, wide of off. Alex Carey leaves it alone.
FOUR! Welcome boundary for Australia! A length ball, on the pads, Green tickles it fine to the fine leg fence.
Short in length, on off. Green blocks it out.
Short of a length, on off. Green looks to defend but it goes off the slice to point, well short of the fielder.
A full ball now, on off. Green pushes it to mid on.
On a length, on off. Defended out.
Short in length,on off. Carey taps it to point and takes a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
Back of a length, outside off. Green taps it to covers.
A length ball, on off. Green defends it out. Oh wait. Stokes has overstepped that. It has been called a NO BALL by the third umpire.
Shorter one this time. Cameron Green ducks under it and lets that go through.
Shaping back in a tad bit. A length ball, on the pads. Cameron Green looks to block this but misses and the ball hit him on the pads and rolls towards point.
Tad fuller, on middle. Green lunges and defends it out.
On a length, outside off. Cameron Green blocks it solidly.

AUSTRALIA ARE EVENTUALLY INTO THE LEAD. Did not feel that we will use that word eventually, when they were 76/1. And Ben Stokes is frustrated and furious with his luck. He charges in and goes full around off and generates an outside edge straightaway, as Green looks to defend. But it dies down on its way towards gully and manages to get past the diving fielder at third slip. Haseeb Hameed chases it down from gully and the batsmen return for the second. Stokes is fired up here.
Ben Stokes has the ball now. His figures till now read (6-1-23-0)
Good-length, outside off. Alex Carey defends it out. A maiden for James Anderson.
Change of angle this time. James Anderson goes over the wicket, serves a length ball, on leg. Alex Carey blocks it on the leg side.
Tad fuller, outside off. Alex Carey leans and pushes it towards mid on.
Good-length, around the off pole. Carey taps it to point.
Anderson pulls his length back here, on leg. Alex Carey, on his toes, defends it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Alex Carey strides forward and blocks it towards cover.
Length and angling on the pads. Green flicks it in front of square leg for a brace.
Length ball, way outside off. Left alone.
On middle. Green looks to block it on the leg side but gets a soft leading edge back on the deck.
Pacy stuff from Wood! Hurls a short ball now, on middle. Green sits under it.
Short in length, outside off. Green blocks it off the back foot.

Mark Wood showing his skills here! A length ball, on middle, it lands and shoots off the deck. Green looks to defend but gets hit on the gloves. The ball lobs and drops well in front of the man at point.
On a length and on middle. Carey gets on his toes and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Short in length, around off, Green pushes it through covers for a single.
On middle. Green pushes it back to Anderson who gets low to grab it.
Length again, on off. Green with solid defense. England have been rock solid with their bowling. Not many freebies given and look so sharp here.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
On middle, on a length, Green pushes it back to Anderson who shows his foot skills to collect it.
Good leave! Carey covers his off stump and lets this length ball through to the keeper.
On a length, on off. Carey defends it towards point now.
Short of a length, on middle. Carey keeps it out.
On middle, on a length, tucked away to square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Wood generating some extra pace here. This was on a length and way outside off. Green has a poke at it away from the body and he misses it completely.
Short in length, around the 4th stump channel. Green blocks it towards cover.
Mark Wood (12-2-46-1) is back into the attack.
Wicket-maiden over! Excellent stuff from James Anderson. Touch fuller, on off, pushed to mid off.
Steep bounce from Anderson, around off. Carey gets hit on the gloves as he looks to defend it.
Anderson continues to bowl in the outside off channel. Carey lets it through to the keeper.
Length again, outside off. Carey leaves it alone.
On a length, coming back in with the angle, outside off. Carey shoulders arms to it.
Alex Carey walks in now, at number 8, replacing Marcus Harris.

OUT! Edged and taken and the master strikes! This is precisely what England needed. Get the set batsman out. On a fuller length, around off, Harris has been leaving those all morning off Robinson but Jimmy is a different cup of tea. Marcus thinks he has to play at it and even then, he does so pretty late. But the ball straightens just that tad and takes the outside edge. Straight into the hands of the skipper, Joe Root, at first slip. The long vigil of Harris comes to an end. One of the rare occasions of a genuinely good ball getting a batsman out. Normally, it is a build-up which leads to a false stroke. Nothing false from Harris on that occasion. Australia 6 down, still trail by 5. For the first time in this series, England are in a great position in this series. Can they keep Australia to under 220?
Commentary.Howout: c Joe Root b James Anderson

Commentary.Commentary: Flatter and around off. Green stays solid in his defense, this time on the back foot.
Short again, on middle. Defended out.
Now goes back and punches it to point. This was short and on off.
A loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Three taken! Pitches it up, outside off. Harris leans and drives it through point. Mark Wood gives a chase and cuts it off.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Harris prods and blocks it out.
Tad shorter, outside off. Cameron Green, on back foot, looks to defend but gets an inside edge on to the thigh pads.
Full in length, around off. Cameron Green strides forward and pushes it towards cover.
Very full, on the pads. Green looks to flicks this, but gets an outside edge to the man at point.
Full length, on middle. Cameron Green defends that one.
Swinging it away this time, fuller, around middle. Cameron Green pushes it back to the bowler. Still no signs of any offensive shot. Green getting used to the pitch before unleashing.
James Anderson serves a full-length delivery, around off. Marcus Harris taps it towards mid on for a quick single.

Joe Root calls his best bowler now as James Anderson is back into the attack.  15-7-22-2 so far. His previous spell, which we witnessed this morning, was his longest and the best so far, in this series. 6-5-1-1 it read.
Shorter this time, outside off. Cameron Green hangs back and chops it to the man at point.
Flighting it up again, on middle. Cameron Green lunges and blocks it watchfully.
Tossing it up again, around off. Cameron Green drives it towards cover.
Loopy delivery, goes fuller this time. Marcus Harris leans and pushes it towards long on for a single.
Slower this time, darting it on the pads. Marcus Harris, on back foot, tucks it towards fine leg for a brace.
Quicker through the air, down the leg. Marcus Harris lets that go, Jos Buttler fails to collect that.

DRINKS BREAK. Something to feel better about for England while having that hourly sip. It just seemed to be going flat post Lunch but Robinson has managed to get a wicket at the right time (not that there is ever a wrong time). But cannot understand the tactics from Root. He continues to persist with Leach, who, in turn, continues to persist with that negative line around leg stump.
